CHARTER.docx.description:
This Charter Party Agreement is a formal maritime contract governing the chartering of a vessel between a Shipowner and a Charterer for the transportation of goods by sea. It defines the commercial, operational, and legal terms of the charter, including vessel details, charter type, freight or hire rates, laytime, demurrage, loading and discharge ports, cargo specifications, responsibilities of each party, and applicable maritime laws.

The template is suitable for voyage charter, time charter, or bareboat charter arrangements and is designed for use in international shipping, oil and gas transportation, bulk commodities, and general cargo trades. It follows standard maritime and commercial practices and is intended for pre-fixture negotiations, contract finalization, and operational execution.
